<document>
  <properties>
    <title>ECM Website Development</title>
  </properties>
  <body>
    <section name="The JSP tag library">
      <subsection name="Importing the taglib">
        <p>The taglib definition file is present as <code>/META-INF/hst.tld</code> within the
          included HST jar file (see <a href="getting.html">getting the HST packages</a>) and
          should be found by your web server. The URI of the taglib is
          <code>http://www.hippoecm.org/jsp/hst</code> so to import the taglib in your jsp use the
          piece of code below. As prefix we recommend <code>hst</code>, as a simple <code>h</code>
          is commonly used for jsf html tags.</p>
        <source><![CDATA[<%@ taglib uri="http://www.hippoecm.org/jsp/hst" prefix="hst" %>]]></source>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Tags">
        <p>The following tags are available:</p>
        <table cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0">
          <tr>
            <th>Tag</th>
            <th>Description</th>
            <th>Uses URL mapping?</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/content-tag.html">&lt;hst:content&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Gets the value of a property from a context object.</td>
            <td>No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/context-tag.html">&lt;hst:context&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Creates a new context object from an existing one and a location.</td>
            <td>No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/encodeurl-tag.html">&lt;hst:encodeURL&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Encodes a repository path location to a URL valid for URL mapping.</td>
            <td>Yes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/include-tag.html">&lt;hst:include&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Includes in the page the output for a certain repository location, as found via
              the URL mapping functionality.</td>
            <td>Yes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/documents-tag.html">&lt;hst:documents&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Show a list of documents from a repository location.</td>
            <td>Yes, overridable</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/documents-tag.html">&lt;hst:news&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Show a list of news items from a repository location.</td>
            <td>Yes, overridable</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/documents-tag.html">&lt;hst:events&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Show a list of events from a repository location.</td>
            <td>Yes, overridable</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/documents-tag.html">&lt;hst:articles&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Show a list of articles from a repository location.</td>
            <td>Yes, overridable</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/menu-tag.html">&lt;hst:menu&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Shows a dynamic menu as read from content in the repository.</td>
            <td>Yes, overridable</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/sitemap-tag.html">&lt;hst:siteMap&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Shows a dynamic site map as read from content in the repository.</td>
            <td>Yes, overridable</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>
